t:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0in;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Mr. Samuels, Ms. Levine, Mr. Nedd, Beth, Dan and Tim S. on 1/5/11 regarding the Geospatial Publication Investment(GPI) and its scope.&nbsp; The GPI team proposed creating a Bureau wide effort instead of just a WO 300 effort.&nbsp; Ms. Levine and Mr. Need both agreed that it was a good goal.&nbsp; Ms. Levine reinforced that WO 300 needs to work with the other Directorates in order to gain buy in.&nbsp; Ms. Levine also stated that she wants an end user team established with a team lead.&nbsp; Beth agreed that this was a good idea and feasible.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Ms. Levine also announced that the ITIB will be postponed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Discussed the creation of a formal user group on 1/5/11 with Beth and Al\'Tariq.&nbsp; Beth thinks this is a great idea because it will ensure requirements are gathered while maintaining a balance between WO 300, WO 500 and users.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Beth requested additional information regarding a presentation that  Patrick did.&nbsp; I will work with Patrick when he returns to gather  information.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Submitted email request to Mr. Smauels on 1/3/11 in regards to the status of the New Media strategy.&nbsp; He provided a verbal response that he had not submitted the newest version to the teams.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other</strong></p>\r\n<p>Attended staff meeting on 1/4/11. Mr. Samuels emphasized the need to understand WO 500 goals and the roles that each of us play.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/4/11 to discuss GPI\'s status.&nbsp; We looked at strategy\'s to ensure that we were pursuing the best approach since we inserted GPI into SLM after the project had started.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred to discuss NOC\'s concerns on 1/6/11.&nbsp; He stated that they were concerned that agile development meant that they had to start at the beginning each time they started a new module.&nbsp; Fred provided clarification that they do not need to and that projects can easily proceed with agile development.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Unified Communication</strong></p>\r\n<p>Provided Mohammad a presentation  regarding how to present it to upper management.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Compiled slides for WO 300\'s presentation on 1/4/11.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Prepared a status presentation to present to Ms.  Levine on 1/4/11.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Met with Mohammad on 1/4/11 to dicuss NISMS  and GPI scopes.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Mr. Samuels, Ms. Levine, Mr. Nedd, Beth, Dan and Tim S. on 1/5/11 regarding the Geospatial Publication Investment(GPI) and its scope.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Submitted email request to Mr.  Smauels on 1/3/11 in regards to the status of the New Media strategy.&nbsp;  He provided a verbal response that he had not submitted the newest  version to the teams.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on  1/4/11 to discuss GPI\'s status.&nbsp; We looked at strategy\'s to ensure that  we were pursuing the best approach since we inserted GPI into SLM after  the project had started.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Unified Communication</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Mohammad to  discuss Unified Communication on 1/3/11.&nbsp; Forwarded him a presentation  regarding how to present it to upper management.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met  with Beth 1/4/11 regarding WO 300\'s presentation to Mike Nedd regarding  the status and the scope concerns.&nbsp; Compiled slides for their afternoon  presentation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Al\'Tariq, Mr. Lewis and myself met with Ms. Levine on 1/4/11 to discuss  GPI and AFMSS.&nbsp; Ms. Levine reviewed the information and informed us that  the ITIB would likely be postponed.&nbsp; She informed us that user groups  needed to be part of our effort and that a lead should be chosen outside  of WO300 and WO500.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Mohammad on 1/4/11 to dicuss NISMS  and GPI scopes.&nbsp; He was unsure of NISMS scope so we could not define  overlap.&nbsp; We disussed the need for a site where everyone could share  information about projects they are working on and the status.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Mr. Samuels, Ms. Levine, Mr. Nedd, Beth, Dan and Tim S. on 1/5/11 regarding the Geospatial Publication Investment(GPI) and its scope.&nbsp; The GPI team proposed creating a Bureau wide effort instead of just a WO 300 effort.&nbsp; Ms. Levine and Mr. Need both agreed that it was a good goal.&nbsp; Ms. Levine reinforced that WO 300 needs to work with the other Directorates in order to gain buy in.&nbsp; Ms. Levine also stated that she wants an end user team established with a team lead.&nbsp; Beth agreed that this was a good idea and feasible.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Ms. Levine also announced that the ITIB will be postponed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other</strong></p>\r\n<p>Attended staff meeting on 1/4/11. Mr. Samuels emphasized the need to understand WO 500 goals and the roles that each of us play.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on  1/4/11 to discuss GPI\'s status.&nbsp; We looked at strategy\'s to ensure that  we were pursuing the best approach since we inserted GPI into SLM after  the project had started.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred to discuss NOC\'s  concerns on 1/6/11.&nbsp; He stated that they were concerned that agile  development meant that they had to start at the beginning each time they  started a new module.&nbsp; Fred provided clarification that they do not  need to and that projects can easily proceed with agile development.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>na</p>', '<p>na</p>', '2', '4', '2012-01-06 18:38:49', null, '2012-01-13 18:01:10');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('13', '6', '1', '1', '2012-01-06', '<ul>\r\n<li>Assisted Naomi to prepare for a GeoComm project status brief with Ms. Levine.</li>\r\n<li>Made last changes to the draft SLM Acquisition Strategy template for now. &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Made last changes to the draft SLM Business Case template for now.</li>\r\n<li>Made last changes to the draft SLM Project Charter template for now.</li>\r\n<li>Had a few more discussions with Mr. Leonard Gore (from BLM GIS group) to discuss their current need for help in the area of GIS.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Had a WO-570 staff meeting</li>\r\n<li>Had a phone conference with the NOC</li>\r\n<li>Had a meeting status update from Mr. Samuels regarding a previous with GPI/GeoComm as their status in SLM</li>\r\n<li>Still worked on getting together some records management templates that we can add to the SLM repository. &nbsp;Currently we do not have any and have not found any to use. &nbsp;Will check with DOI to see if they have available template we can use.</li>\r\n<li>Made some changes to the SLM IM that Lauren gave back to me because the reviewer needed some clarity in one of the paragraphs. &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Reviewed the NOC SLM diagram that Gail sent me. &nbsp;Working on a list of question to send Gail regarding this diagram</li>\r\n<li>Review some GPI email (to get caught up with where they currently are)</li>\r\n<li>Reviewed &nbsp;one of BLM&rsquo;s Geo Spatial web portals that is currently under development.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Working on making the last changes to the SLM artifacts based on the changes I last made to the SLM technical handbook.</li>\r\n<li>Reviewed the roles and responsibilities for Walk the Walk Project Lead and Deputy Project Lead for out internal Support/Process Systems project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Completed making changes to the draft SLM Acquisition Strategy template for now.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Completed making changes to the draft SLM Business Case template for now.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Completed making changes to the draft SLM Project Charter template for now.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Completed looking at the last two GeoComm documents for Naomi.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Had a phone conference with the NOC to discuss the latest version of the SLM technical manual 1-5-12. Had a phone conference with Gail, Dan and Preston (the other part of our SLM team) at the NOC to discuss and answer questions about their concerns with the latest version of the SLM.&nbsp; Gail and her team were under the impression that the SLM process did not support the Agile method of development.&nbsp; This was a big concern because of other constraints and restrictions they have to conform to.&nbsp; After providing clarity and examples of how the process was designed to use the NOC team was clear that the SLM does support Agile development.&nbsp; The meeting was very good and I will keep the NOC updated with where we are with getting the SLM process approved. &nbsp;The NOC and to have a face to face via VTC before the end of January 2012.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Met with Mr. Samuels to discuss the latest meeting with Ms. Levine regarding GPI/GeoComm 1-5-12. &nbsp;We discuss a variety of topics from SLM, current BLM systems/programs to BLM culture, and AFMSS.&nbsp; The main purpose of the discussion was to inform me that Ms. Levine want to represent the current status of GPI/GeoComm using the swirl diagrams that we used when we gave her the SLM presentation a few months ago.&nbsp; I&rsquo;ll have to get the status from Naomi and see how we can incorporate the GPI/GeoComm status information in that type of diagram.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Met with Mr. Leonard Gore and 2 others to discuss the use of GIS in their area 1-3-12. &nbsp;They discuss area that they need help in (using resources more effective)</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Met with Mr. Leonard Gore briefly to clarify our discussion the day before 1-5-12. They wanted to know they can better use existing resources (Enterprise GIS) and how BLM can better use its people and technology</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Had our WO-570 staff meeting 1-4-12.&nbsp; Gave a status/update of what we are currently working on.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #fafafa; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">None at this time</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #fafafa; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">None at this time</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2', '4', '2012-01-06 20:06:31', '6', '2012-01-13 18:02:19');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('14', '6', '1', '1', '2012-01-13', '<ul>\r\n<li>Still worked on getting together some records management templates that we can add to the SLM repository. &nbsp;Currently we do not have any and have not found any to use. &nbsp;Will check with DOI to see if they have available template we can use.</li>\r\n<li>Working on a list of question to send Gail regarding this diagram</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Still working on making the last changes to some of the SLM artifacts based on the changes I last made to the SLM technical handbook.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Had discussion with Naomi and Mr. Lewis regarding the GeoComm project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Working on making some suggestion for the GeoComm project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Working on making a list of suggested next actions for the GeoComm project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Checked on the status of the SLM IM. &nbsp;Currently there is no new updated status for the SLM IM.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Had discussion with Naomi as regards to the New Media Project.</li>\r\n<li>From and SLM perspective: Currently looking into (researching) what it will take to pull together a basic Enterprise Architecture (EA) program. EA is very critical and is a required component of the SLM process. Projects cannot successfully progress through the SLM process without involving the area of EA.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</p>', '<ul>\r\n<li>Completed making a good number of changes to the SLM technical manual in an effort to finalize this draft version before it goes out to be reviewed.</li>\r\n<li>Completed doing some basic research on Enterprise Architecture programs. &nbsp;Will need to do some further investigations on this.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Had several conversations/discussions with Naomi through the week regarding the current status of GeoComm. 1-9-2012 through 1-13-2012. &nbsp;Had several discussion and brainstorming session as to how to get the GeoComm group moving forward to they can make progress. We came up with several options that we need to discuss with Mr. Samuels before we make the recommendation to the GeoComm group. &nbsp;As soon as complete and outline our suggestions/recommendations we will be submitting them to Mr. Samuels for his review and feedback.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Had a discussion with Naomi and Mr. Lewis 1-10-2012. &nbsp;Discussed the best way to get everyone that is a support system to GeoComm onboard and apart of the process for building the new GeoComm system.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Had a discussion/meeting with Naomi on 1-11-2012 regarding the need for a strong Enterprise Architecture (EA) program in order to ensure projects efforts are not duplicated and also having the ability to take advantage (piggy back) of an existing system.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Had a meeting with Naomi regarding the New Media project 1-12-2012. Had a brainstorming session with Naomi as to making some recommendation/suggestions as how the New Media project should proceed. &nbsp;Discussed how they need to better define the communication problem they are looking to fix before getting too far down the process, discussed which groups of people are they trying to improve communications with. &nbsp; Discussed how they currently communicate with these groups and how do they envision to communicate with these groups in the future.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>', '<p>None at this time.</p>', '<p>None at this time.</p>', '2', '1', '2012-01-13 22:04:09', null, '2012-02-03 19:57:11');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('15', '3', '2', '1', '2012-01-13', '<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Began  updating the ITIB presentation on 1/9/12 to include updated scope and  ensure that it is worded broadly enough for executives per Ms. Levines  request during the WO 300 and WO 500 meeting.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth and the GPI team on 1/13/12 via conference call to discuss the overall status and the scope as agreed upon by WO 300 and WO 500.&nbsp;  The most immediate concern is for WO 300 to provide a clear scope.&nbsp; It  is best to consider modular development to meet business needs in a  logical manner.&nbsp; There is a concern about interim solutions.&nbsp; I spoke  with Al\'Tariq and we are going to review the IM preventing development  in other program areas at this point.</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with Michelle Thomas on 1/10/12 to dicuss the New Media Strategy. She stated that she believed that stakeholder engagement is very different from Public Affairs which is the same assessment Ronnie has made.&nbsp; Michelle believes that WO 600 does govern what is formally posted but other interactions fall within a gray area and the roles in that area should be shared by WO 500 &amp; WO 600 because Kaveh is using the &ldquo;BLM can&rsquo;t&rdquo; in areas where BLM may be allowed.&nbsp; (When sharing this information, she asked that we not state that &ldquo;Michelle said&rdquo; because she still works with Kaveh).</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>Researched internal New Media proof of concept and sent a proposal  via email to Al\'Tariq on 1/12/12.&nbsp; The research included meeting with  Fred on 1/12/12 to discuss available technologies.</p>\r\n<p>Al\'Tariq  provided a copy of WO 600\'s (Kaveh\'s) email regarding the New Media  Strategy on 1/12/12.&nbsp; The email stated that WO 600 would not support the  strategy as currently written. I provided email feedback to Al\'Tariq on  1/12/12 regarding points that were not necessarily accurate to the  strategy.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq on 1/13/12 to discuss the New Media  Strategy overall and how to work with WO 600 to gain support.&nbsp; We  discussed the overall pupose and possibly pursuing an internal proof of  concept only&nbsp; at this time and it may provide us a basis to provide a  stakeholder engagement proof of concept at a later date. We also  discussed what we could agree to in WO 600\'s email. I will provide  Al\'Tariq with some feedback on how to reword items.</p>\r\n<p>Worked with Kyla on 1/13/12 to revise the Strategy.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/11/12 to discuss  the need for a strong EA in order to ensure projects arent duplicated  and arent conflicting in general.</p>', '<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Began  updating the ITIB presentation on 1/9/12 to include updated scope and  ensure that it is worded broadly enough for executives per Ms. Levines  request during the WO 300 and WO 500 meeting.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth and the GPI team on 1/13/12 via conference call to discuss the overall status and the scope as agreed upon by WO 300 and WO 500.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with Michelle Thomas on 1/10/12 to dicuss the New Media Strategy. </span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>Researched internal New Media proof of concept and sent a proposal  via email to Al\'Tariq on 1/12/12.&nbsp; The research included meeting with  Fred on 1/12/12 to discuss available technologies.</p>\r\n<p>Provided email feedback to Al\'Tariq on  1/12/12 regarding points that were not necessarily accurate to the  strategy in regards to WO 600\'s email.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq on 1/13/12 to discuss the New Media  Strategy overall and how to work with WO 600 to gain support.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Worked with Kyla on 1/13/12 to revise the Strategy.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/11/12 to discuss  the need for a strong EA in order to ensure projects arent duplicated  and arent conflicting in general.</p>', '<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth and the GPI team on 1/13/12 via conference call to discuss the overall status and the scope as agreed upon by WO 300 and WO 500.&nbsp;  The most immediate concern is for WO 300 to provide a clear scope.&nbsp; It  is best to consider modular development to meet business needs in a  logical manner.&nbsp; There is a concern about interim solutions.&nbsp; I spoke  with Al\'Tariq and we are going to review the IM preventing development  in other program areas at this point.</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with Michelle Thomas on 1/10/12 to dicuss the New Media Strategy. She stated that she believed that stakeholder engagement is very different from Public Affairs which is the same assessment Ronnie has made.&nbsp; Michelle believes that WO 600 does govern what is formally posted but other interactions fall within a gray area and the roles in that area should be shared by WO 500 &amp; WO 600 because Kaveh is using the &ldquo;BLM can&rsquo;t&rdquo; in areas where BLM may be allowed.&nbsp; (When sharing this information, she asked that we not state that &ldquo;Michelle said&rdquo; because she still works with Kaveh).</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq on 1/13/12 to discuss the New Media  Strategy overall and how to work with WO 600 to gain support.&nbsp; We  discussed the overall pupose and possibly pursuing an internal proof of  concept only&nbsp; at this time and it may provide us a basis to provide a  stakeholder engagement proof of concept at a later date. We also  discussed what we could agree to in WO 600\'s email. I will provide  Al\'Tariq with some feedback on how to reword items.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/11/12 to discuss  the need for a strong EA in order to ensure projects arent duplicated  and arent conflicting in general.</p>', '<p>na</p>', '<p>na</p>', '2', '4', '2012-01-13 22:38:07', '3', '2012-01-20 00:23:26');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('16', '3', '2', '1', '2012-01-20', '<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Provided revised bullets on 1/17/12 to the email provided by Kaveh in regards to WO 600\'s support of the New Media Strategy.</p>\r\n<p>Met  with Al\'Tariq on 1/17/12 to discuss WO 600\'s/Kaveh\'s email.&nbsp; He thought  the revised bullets were a good idea and has a meeting scheduled with  Kaveh on 1/17/12.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq on 1/18/12 to discuss New Media Strategy status and meeting with Ronnie.&nbsp; We discussed the Next Steps and Concerns from WO 600.&nbsp; Updated presentation to include Ronnies Next Steps and the Interdiciplinary Teams Next Steps along with a slide noting major concerns for meeting with Ronnie on 1/18/12.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Met with Ronnie and Al\'Tariq on 1/18/12 to discuss presentation and meeting with the Exective Team.&nbsp; Ronnie approved the presentaiton and requested that the Next Steps slide be combined.&nbsp; She also requested that we meet with the executives individually prior to a meeting with the entire team.&nbsp; This includes a meetin with NPS and Neil Kornze.</p>\r\n<p>Updated presentation for the Executive Team on 1/19/12 to include combined Next Steps and deleted the Concerns slide.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed NPS\'s&nbsp; most recent updates the their Social Media Policy on 1/19/12 and sent an email to Ms. Levine and Al\'Tariq noting concerns that their process does not align with the process that she has discussed. The email asked if she was still interested in the meeting under these circumstances.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discussed the postponed ITIB with Rich D. on 1/17/12. He stated that there would probaly be a meeting towards the end on February.</p>\r\n<p>Provided Beth with information on 1/1712 regarding the ITIB and provided feedback to her concerns regarding the scope of the Investment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/17/12 to discuss Acquisition Strategy documentation after noticing several existing versions in other areas of BLM.&nbsp; Fred is reviewing the documents.<strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/19/12 to discuss sharepoint sites where SLM documents and PMO documents were posted.&nbsp; The SLM documents posted are not part of the current SLM.&nbsp; Fred stated that he would discuss this with Al\'Tariq.&nbsp; The PMO documents reflect a similar process to SLM.&nbsp; We discussed the confusion of having two processes that are duplicating efforts.&nbsp; Fred stated that he would look into this further.</p>', '<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Provided revised bullets on 1/17/12 to the email provided by Kaveh in regards to WO 600\'s support of the New Media Strategy.</p>\r\n<p>Met  with Al\'Tariq on 1/17/12 to discuss WO 600\'s/Kaveh\'s email.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Updated presentation to  include Ronnies Next Steps and the Interdiciplinary Teams Next Steps  along with a slide noting major concerns for meeting with Ronnie on  1/18/12.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Met with Ronnie and Al\'Tariq on 1/18/12 to discuss  presentation and meeting with the Exective Team.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Updated presentation for the Executive Team on 1/19/12 to include combined Next Steps and deleted the Concerns slide.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed  NPS\'s&nbsp; most recent updates the their Social Media Policy on 1/19/12 and  sent an email to Ms. Levine and Al\'Tariq noting concerns that their  process does not align with the process that she has discussed. The  email asked if she was still interested in the meeting under these  circumstances.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discussed  the postponed ITIB with Rich D. on 1/17/12. He stated that there would  probaly be a meeting towards the end on February.</p>\r\n<p>Provided Beth with information on 1/1712 regarding the ITIB and provided feedback to her concerns regarding the scope of the Investment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/17/12 to discuss Acquisition Strategy documentation  after noticing several existing versions in other areas of BLM.&nbsp; <strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/19/12 to discuss sharepoint sites where SLM documents and PMO documents were posted.&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met  with Al\'Tariq on 1/17/12 to discuss WO 600\'s/Kaveh\'s email.&nbsp; He thought  the revised bullets were a good idea and has a meeting scheduled with  Kaveh on 1/17/12.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq on 1/18/12 to  discuss New Media Strategy status and meeting with Ronnie.&nbsp; We discussed  the Next Steps and Concerns from WO 600.&nbsp; Updated presentation to  include Ronnies Next Steps and the Interdiciplinary Teams Next Steps  along with a slide noting major concerns for meeting with Ronnie on  1/18/12.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Met with Ronnie and Al\'Tariq on 1/18/12 to discuss  presentation and meeting with the Exective Team.&nbsp; Ronnie approved the  presentaiton and requested that the Next Steps slide be combined.&nbsp; She  also requested that we meet with the executives individually prior to a  meeting with the entire team.&nbsp; This includes a meetin with NPS and Neil  Kornze.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/17/12 to discuss Acquisition Strategy documentation  after noticing several existing versions in other areas of BLM.&nbsp; Fred is  reviewing the documents.<strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/19/12 to discuss sharepoint sites where SLM documents and PMO documents were posted.&nbsp; The SLM documents posted are not part of the current SLM.&nbsp;  Fred stated that he would discuss this with Al\'Tariq.&nbsp; The PMO documents  reflect a similar process to SLM.&nbsp; We discussed the confusion of having  two processes that are duplicating efforts.&nbsp; Fred stated that he would  look into this further.</p>', '<p>na</p>', '<p>na</p>', '2', '4', '2012-01-20 18:09:57', '3', '2012-01-25 03:33:38');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('17', '6', '1', '1', '2012-01-20', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Looked for some records management templates that we can add to the SLM repository. &nbsp;Have not found any at this point.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Had discussion with Naomi regarding the GeoComm project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Working on making a &nbsp;suggestion list for the GeoComm project. &nbsp;Will get this list to Naomi sometime early next week.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Checked on the status of the SLM IM. &nbsp;Currently there is no new updated status for the SLM IM. &nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Had some discussions with Naomi regarding the New Media Project. &nbsp;Will provide Naomi a suggestion list early next week.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Working with Mohammad to restrict access to the existing SLM sharepoint sites. &nbsp;This will greatly help us in preparing to setup the new SLM sharepoint space.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Contacted Gail from the NOC to request comments on the SLM handbook.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Contacted Gail from the NOC to request the agenda and date of when they (the NOC) want to have the WebEx meeting (sometime before the end of January).</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Gave a copy of the SLM handbook and framework diagram for Christina (our new Data Administrator) to review and provide comments</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Reviewed all the Support Process/System documentation provided by Brian in preparation for our meeting on Tuesday of next week.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Corrected some errors in some of the SLM artifacts that I found.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Went through the existing SLM sharepoint sites to review all documents posted there. &nbsp;Some of the documents are useful but most of them can be archived. &nbsp;Will finish review the remainder early next week so we can restrict these sites to only a few people.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #fafafa;\">\r\n<ul style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; margin: 0px;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Had our bi-monthly staff team meeing. 1-18-12. &nbsp;Provided update status of projects I am currently working on.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #fafafa;\">\r\n<ul style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; margin: 0px;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Had a meeting with Naomi regarding the New Media project 1-17-2012. Discussed how they need to better define the communication problem they are looking to fix before getting too far down the process, discussed which groups of people are they trying to improve communications with. &nbsp; Discussed how they currently communicate with these groups and how do they envision to communicate with these groups in the future. &nbsp;We are going to further discuss this issue on next week when we have more time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa;\">None at this time.</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa;\">None at this time.</span></p>', '2', '4', '2012-01-23 15:19:02', '6', '2012-01-25 03:32:15');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('18', '3', '2', '1', '2012-01-27', '<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Requested Marti set up the individual meetings with Ms. Levine and each of the memebrs if Core Team of Executives on 1/23/12.&nbsp; Sent followup requests on 1/24/12 and 1/26/12.&nbsp; Sent requests to Al\'Tariq on 1/26/12 and he followed up with the request on 1/27/12.</p>\r\n<p>Discussed Oregons efforts with Ms. Levine on 1/24/12.&nbsp; Updated New Media Presentation to include Ms. Levines requests and sent it to Ms. Levine on 1/24/12.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed and updated New Media Strategy so that the Next Steps aligned with the presentation on 1/25/12.</p>\r\n<p>Provided feedback to Alexandra Ritchie\'s email request for the status of the New Media Strategy on 1/25/12 per Al\'Tariq\'s request.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth on 1/24/12 to discuss the status of the Investment.&nbsp; There has not been much progress due to her move.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth on 1/26/12 to discuss IM\'s relating to web policies and geospatial data publication.&nbsp; She wanted to ensure that they were within policy boundaries.&nbsp; Worked with Brian Anthony to get a list of applicable IM\'s.&nbsp; Fred also provided me with a link to IM\'s online.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth and GPI team on 1/26/12 to discuss requirements and exisitng systems.&nbsp; To the best of our knowledge, an inventory of existing viewers and mapping services does not exist.&nbsp; We discussed possibilities for collecting the data for the inventory.&nbsp; I provided an email request to Patrick and Al\'tariq to see if we had any type of exisitng information.&nbsp; Patrick responed on 1/27/12 with an additional point of contact.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred and Al\'Tariq on 1/24/12 to discuss CPIC\'s comments in regards to the SLM.&nbsp; Several comments had little applicability. The overall issue seems to be that the process is not owned by their division.&nbsp; Fred is providing a written response to the comments.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/25/12 to further discuss CPIC\'s comments.&nbsp; We discussed ideas on how to provide a proper response to the CPIC team.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Eplanning</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq and Jane Peterson on 1/27/12 to discuss the status of the eplanning investment along with project management concerns in regards to tracking the project and having accountability.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq stated that others had raised similar concerns and he would see where he could address certain issues with the NOC.&nbsp; He also stated that he would like us to put an SLA in place to provide guidance and lessen conflict.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Process Planning Team for the Walk the Walk Initiative on 1/25/12.&nbsp; We discussed the goals of the team and the scope.&nbsp; The scope will include communication regarding projects, IM\'s and FOIA requests. CPIC had prepared a presentation that contradicted the SLM but it was not given due to time constraints. Provided this information to Al\'Tariq.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Xavi on 1/27/12 to discuss Microsoft Project and a Project Plan.&nbsp; Provided examples and templates to Xavi.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Updated New Media Presentation to include Ms. Levines  requests and sent it to Ms. Levine on 1/24/12.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed and updated New Media Strategy so that the Next Steps aligned with the presentation on 1/25/12.</p>\r\n<p>Provided  feedback to Alexandra Ritchie\'s email request for the status of the New  Media Strategy on 1/25/12 per Al\'Tariq\'s request.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Worked with Brian Anthony to get a list of  applicable IM\'s.&nbsp; Fred also provided me with a link to IM\'s online.</p>\r\n<p>Discussed possibilities for  collecting the data for the inventory.&nbsp; I provided an email request to  Patrick and Al\'tariq to see if we had any type of exisitng information.&nbsp;  Patrick responed on 1/27/12 with an additional point of contact.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met  with Process Planning Team for the Walk the Walk Initiative on  1/25/12.&nbsp; We discussed the goals of the team and the scope.&nbsp; The scope  will include communication regarding projects, IM\'s and FOIA requests.  CPIC had prepared a presentation that contradicted the SLM but it was  not given due to time constraints. Provided this information to  Al\'Tariq.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Xavi on 1/27/12 to discuss Microsoft Project and a Project Plan.&nbsp; Provided examples and templates to Xavi.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Eplanning</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq and Jane Peterson  on 1/27/12 to discuss the status of the eplanning investment along with  project management concerns in regards to tracking the project and  having accountability.&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth on 1/24/12 to discuss the status of the Investment.&nbsp; There has not been much progress due to her move.</p>\r\n<p>Met  with Beth on 1/26/12 to discuss IM\'s relating to web policies and  geospatial data publication.&nbsp; She wanted to ensure that they were within  policy boundaries.&nbsp; Worked with Brian Anthony to get a list of  applicable IM\'s.&nbsp; Fred also provided me with a link to IM\'s online.</p>\r\n<p>Met  with Beth and GPI team on 1/26/12 to discuss requirements and exisitng  systems.&nbsp; To the best of our knowledge, an inventory of existing viewers  and mapping services does not exist.&nbsp; We discussed possibilities for  collecting the data for the inventory.&nbsp; I provided an email request to  Patrick and Al\'tariq to see if we had any type of exisitng information.&nbsp;  Patrick responed on 1/27/12 with an additional point of contact.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met  with Fred and Al\'Tariq on 1/24/12 to discuss CPIC\'s comments in regards  to the SLM.&nbsp; Several comments had little applicability. The overall  issue seems to be that the process is not owned by their division.&nbsp; Fred  is providing a written response to the comments.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on  1/25/12 to further discuss CPIC\'s comments.&nbsp; We discussed ideas on how  to provide a proper response to the CPIC team.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met  with Process Planning Team for the Walk the Walk Initiative on  1/25/12.&nbsp; We discussed the goals of the team and the scope.&nbsp; The scope  will include communication regarding projects, IM\'s and FOIA requests.  CPIC had prepared a presentation that contradicted the SLM but it was  not given due to time constraints. Provided this information to  Al\'Tariq.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Xavi on 1/27/12 to discuss Microsoft Project and a Project Plan.&nbsp; Provided examples and templates to Xavi.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Eplanning</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq and Jane Peterson  on 1/27/12 to discuss the status of the eplanning investment along with  project management concerns in regards to tracking the project and  having accountability.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq stated that others had raised similar  concerns and he would see where he could address certain issues with the  NOC.&nbsp; He also stated that he would like us to put an SLA in place to  provide guidance and lessen conflict.</p>', '<p>na</p>', '<p>na</p>', '2', '4', '2012-01-27 18:22:53', '3', '2012-01-31 22:31:32');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('19', '6', '1', '1', '2012-01-27', '<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; background-color: white; line-height: 14.4pt; text-indent: -0.25in;\">Brief meeting with Mr. Samuels and Naomi regarding CPIC comments on the SLM</span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: white; line-height: 14.4pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt;\">Worked on providing a response to CPIC comments on the SLM. &nbsp;Will have Mr. Samuels review the draft response before we submit them to CPIC.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: white; line-height: 14.4pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt;\">Had a Walk the walk meeting with our System Support.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: white; line-height: 14.4pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt;\">Had a brief meeting with Naomi to review CPIC comments to the SLM.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: white; line-height: 14.4pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt;\">Conversation via email with Gail from the NOC regarding their comments on the SLM. &nbsp;They will submit their comments in the near future.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: white; line-height: 14.4pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt;\">Got help from Ken and Mike to find the location of where all IM\'s are located.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: white; line-height: 14.4pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt;\">Completed a brief presention of the definitions that we have to present to Ms. Levine.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: white; line-height: 14.4pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt;\">Fixing some error/corrections with the SLM submitted by our Data Administrator.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: 14.4pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>', '<ul>\r\n<li>Completed reviewing CPIC comments and have begun drafting our response.</li>\r\n<li>Completed a presention of the definitions that we have to present to Ms. Levine next week sometime.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -0.25in;\">Brief meeting with Mr. Samuels and Naomi regarding CPIC comments on the SLM 1-24-12.&nbsp;</span>Discussed how to respond to CPIC comments.&nbsp; Many of the comments had no basis or did not make any sense. Drafting our response and will have Mr. Samuels review them.</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -0.25in;\">Had a Walk the walk meeting with our System Support to discuss the team charter and purpose. 1-24-12</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -0.25in;\">Had a brief meeting with Naomi to review CPIC comments to the SLM. 1-23-12. We reviewed CPIC comments on the SLM in preparation to have a discussion with Mr. Samuels.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -0.25in;\">Conversation via email with Gail from the NOC regarding their comments on the SLM.&nbsp; 1-26-12.&nbsp;</span>They will submit their comments in the near future.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>None at this time.</p>', '<p>None at this time.</p>', '2', '4', '2012-01-30 15:55:38', '6', '2012-01-31 22:32:35');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('20', '6', '1', '1', '2012-02-03', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Worked on providing a response to CPIC comments on the SLM. &nbsp;Will have Mr. Samuels review the draft response before we submit them to CPIC.</li>\r\n<li>Made some minor corrections to the SLM technical manual.</li>\r\n<li>Working on the SLM presenation for Ms. Levine that will contain the next few phases for her to review. &nbsp;We will be presenting this to her soon.</li>\r\n<li>Helped Mike review some software tools for a project he is working on.</li>\r\n<li>Worked on making some additional changes to the SLM handbook based on reviews from other reviewers.</li>\r\n<li>Worked on making a list of suggestions for our Walk the Walk Support group.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Completed a draft response to CPIC comments on the SLM and submitted draft to Mr. Samuels.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Had a meeting with Naomi to provide some wording to some of CPIC comments to the SLM as it relates to the PMBOC. 2-2-12</li>\r\n<li>Had a meeting with Mike to help him review some software tools for a project he is working on. 2-2-12</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>None at this time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>None at this time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2', '4', '2012-02-03 18:29:25', '6', '2012-02-11 00:35:48');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('21', '3', '2', '1', '2012-02-03', '<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Finalized meeting with Neil, Ronnie and Janet along with a meeting with Ronnie and Carole Pfisterer Carter on 1/30/12.&nbsp; The meetings are scheduled for 2/16/12.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq on 1/31/12 to discuss his meeting with Kaveh regarding his stance on the New Media Strategy.&nbsp; Kaveh conveyed that he and WO 600 would not support a New Media Strategy where internal and external efforts were combined.&nbsp; He stated that they had to be two separate strategies and that the external strategy would come from WO 600. I expressed concern that Ronnie is unaware of this as we move forward with the additional meetings.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq stated that he agreed that Ronnie needed to be made aware and that he would share the information with her.&nbsp; He also asked that I review the Strategy again and ensure that WO 600\'s objectives are incorporated.&nbsp; I reviewed the Strategy, ensured incorporation of all objectives and added WO-600\'s \'Strategies\' under Next Steps.&nbsp; This was submitted to Al\'Tariq for review on 2/1/12 for review.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tablets/Smartphones</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Brian and Al\'Tariq to discuss items needed for the Tablet and Smartphone Inventory on 1/31/12.&nbsp; Created a spreadsheet for tracking of Tablets and Iphones including a section for business need.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discussed the need for a clear written scope with Beth on 2/1/12.&nbsp; Provided her with a request for a meeting on 2/3/12.&nbsp; We will be meeting on Tuesday 2/7/12.&nbsp; Provided her with notification that the ITIB will meet on 3/1/12.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Quicktime IM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Prepared an IM for the release of an application for remote access to Quicktime per Al\'Tariq\'s request on 2/2/12.&nbsp; Submitted it to Al\'Tariq on 2/2/12 and followed up with a meeting to discuss the language.&nbsp; He approved the IM but we did not have access to the needed attachments for the IM.&nbsp; Coordinated with DOI to get the needed attachments for the IM.&nbsp; Worked with Lauren on 2/3/12 to package the IM. This included preparation of a Note to Reviewer.&nbsp; Prepared an email on 2/3/12 announcing the release of the application and submitted it to Al\'Tariq for review.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 2/1/12 and 2/2/12 to discuss CPIC\'s comments regarding the SLM.&nbsp; Reviewed responses and provided responses to Fred that were specific to Project Management Insitute\'s (PMI\'s) Project Management Body of Knowledge (PMBOK)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Finalized meeting with Neil, Ronnie  and Janet along with a meeting with Ronnie and Carole Pfisterer Carter  on 1/30/12.&nbsp; The meetings are scheduled for 2/16/12.</p>\r\n<p>Met with  Al\'Tariq on 1/31/12 to discuss his meeting with Kaveh regarding his  stance on the New Media Strategy. He asked that I review the Strategy again and ensure that WO  600\'s objectives are incorporated.&nbsp; Reviewed the Strategy, ensured  incorporation of all objectives and added WO-600\'s \'Strategies\' under  Next Steps.&nbsp; This was submitted to Al\'Tariq for review on 2/1/12 for  review.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tablets/Smartphones</strong></p>\r\n<p>Created a spreadsheet for tracking of Tablets  and Iphones including a section for business need.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discussed  the need for a clear written scope with Beth on 2/1/12.&nbsp; Provided her  with a request for a meeting on 2/3/12.&nbsp; We will be meeting on Tuesday  2/7/12.&nbsp; Provided her with notification that the ITIB will meet on  3/1/12.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Quicktime IM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Prepared an IM for the  release of an application for remote access to Quicktime per Al\'Tariq\'s  request on 2/2/12.&nbsp; Submitted it to Al\'Tariq on 2/2/12 and followed up  with a meeting to discuss the language.&nbsp; He approved the IM but we did  not have access to the needed attachments for the IM.&nbsp; Coordinated with  DOI to get the needed attachments for the IM.&nbsp; Worked with Lauren on  2/3/12 to package the IM. This included preparation of a Note to  Reviewer.&nbsp; Prepared an email on 2/3/12 announcing the release of the  application and submitted it to Al\'Tariq for review.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 2/1/12 and 2/2/12  to discuss CPIC\'s comments regarding the SLM.&nbsp; Reviewed responses and  provided responses to Fred that were specific to Project Management  Insitute\'s (PMI\'s) Project Management Body of Knowledge (PMBOK).</p>', '<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with  Al\'Tariq on 1/31/12 to discuss his meeting with Kaveh regarding his  stance on the New Media Strategy.&nbsp; Kaveh conveyed that he and WO 600  would not support a New Media Strategy where internal and external  efforts were combined.&nbsp; He stated that they had to be two separate  strategies and that the external strategy would come from WO 600. I  expressed concern that Ronnie is unaware of this as we move forward with  the additional meetings.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq stated that he agreed that Ronnie  needed to be made aware and that he would share the information with  her.&nbsp; He also asked that I review the Strategy again and ensure that WO  600\'s objectives are incorporated.&nbsp; I reviewed the Strategy, ensured  incorporation of all objectives and added WO-600\'s \'Strategies\' under  Next Steps.&nbsp; This was submitted to Al\'Tariq for review on 2/1/12 for  review.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tablets/Smartphones</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with  Brian and Al\'Tariq to discuss items needed for the Tablet and Smartphone  Inventory on 1/31/12.&nbsp; Created a spreadsheet for tracking of Tablets  and Iphones including a section for business need.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Quicktime IM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq on 2/2/12 to discuss the language in the Quicktime IM.&nbsp; He approved the IM but we did  not have access to the needed attachments for the IM.&nbsp; Coordinated with  DOI to get the needed attachments for the IM.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 2/1/12 and 2/2/12  to discuss CPIC\'s comments regarding the SLM.&nbsp; Reviewed responses and  provided responses to Fred that were specific to Project Management  Insitute\'s (PMI\'s) Project Management Body of Knowledge (PMBOK)</p>', '<p>na</p>', '<p>na</p>', '2', '4', '2012-02-03 21:46:45', null, '2012-02-11 00:34:14');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('22', '6', '1', '1', '2012-02-10', '<ul>\r\n<li>Worked on the remaining sections of the SLM presentation. &nbsp;Will submit the presentation to Mr. Samuels as soon as I finish for his review.</li>\r\n<li>Review the&nbsp;Walk the Walk Support Team project plan in preparation for our team meeting.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Started cleaning up my area.</li>\r\n<li>Started organizing files that I have been working on so I can put them on the BLM share drive.</li>\r\n<li>Getting together all BLM file that I have been working on so I can put them on the BLM network (S: drive)</li>\r\n<li>Sent Mr. Lewis and Mr. Springfield emails of the location of where I put all the files I have been working on.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n<li>Completed the SLM presentation and emailed it to Mr. Samuels. &nbsp;The presentation contained the remainder of the SLM phases (Requirements Analysis through Disposition) that will need to be presented to Ms. Levine for her approval.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Put all BLM file that I have been working on onto the shared drive on the BLM network (S: drive)</li>\r\n<li>Sent Mr. Lewis and Mr. Springfield emails of the location of where I put all the files I have been working on.</li>\r\n<li>Almost finished cleaning up my work area.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n<li>2-7-12: Had a meeting with our Walk the Walk Support Team to review and discuss the project plan for the project and our group. &nbsp;The project plan did not have sufficient information for us to complete the task of creating a project timeline. &nbsp;Team lead will look to get the information we need to complet assignment. &nbsp;The team lead will be setting up a demo of the Data Tracking System (DTS) that we discussing during our meeting.</li>\r\n<li>2-8-12: Had a meeting with Mr. Lewis and Mr. Springfield regarding the status of my current contract with Atechra in support of BLM.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>None at this time.</p>', '<p>None at this time.</p>', '2', '4', '2012-02-09 17:53:21', '6', '2012-02-14 17:40:23');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('23', '3', '2', '1', '2012-02-10', '<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Provided Al\'Tariq and Ronnie with information from DOI regarding New Media and Twitter on 2/6/12.<strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Ronnie, Bob Abbey, Kevah, Celia, Craig, Neil and several other BLM staff to review Social Media presentations from California, Colorado and Oregon on 2/7/12.&nbsp; Ronnie requested that I provide the latest New Media presentation so that she could present our work eventhough the Core Team of Executives had not reviewed this.&nbsp; I notified her that WO 600 may not agree with all of the Next Steps per previous conversations.&nbsp; Kaveh presented a External New Media Strategy at the meeting which was closely related to the strategy that his team presented in regards to the overall strategy.&nbsp; He had not shared that he would be presenting this.&nbsp; Neil and Mr. Abbey both liked the states presentations, especially Oregon.&nbsp; They are interested in seeing the Washington Office provide an effort that integrates both internal and external items. .</p>\r\n<p>Provided updated New Media Strategy and Presentation to Al\'Tariq on 2/8/12.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Offsite With Ronnie</strong></p>\r\n<p>Attended off-site meeting in Falls Church Va with Ronnie Levine, Lara Douglas and Ore Fashola at Noblis on 2/7/12.&nbsp; We discussed solutions that they had provided to other government entities.&nbsp; The took us through several technology simulations.&nbsp; Ronnie and I discussed how projects such as GPI and AFMSS could benefit from outside technical consulting due to their complexity and the availability of new technology.&nbsp; If we limit solutions to just what we know, we limit the projects.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discussed the need for the updated Charter and Scope Statement for GPI with Beth on 2/6/12.&nbsp; We scheduled a meeting for 2/8/12.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Beth and Dan on 2/8/12 to discuss the status of GPI and what exactly was needed for the ITIB.&nbsp; We compiled a list of the following questions and submitted them to Al\'Tariq: WO 300 will need and inventory of existing geospatial display applications used across BLM.&nbsp; Who can request that states and other offices submit existing and planned applications and who will handle the registration of these?&nbsp; It is part of the EA function so will WO 500 manage this?&nbsp;&nbsp;The development of new other geospatial display applications is a major concern for this investment because this is a bureau wide effort.&nbsp; If development of separate applications continues, the benefit of having a bureau wide solution is diminished because businesses will have created their own smaller scale solutions that meet their needs without meeting the bureau&rsquo;s need to have a single resource to view the data.&nbsp; However, there is a need for certain application developments in order for businesses to carry on their everyday business.&nbsp; Will WO 300, WO 500 or the ITIB decide which applications are allowed to continue development?&nbsp; Will WO 500 issue policy regarding this because issuing policy is considered a WO 500 function?&nbsp;&nbsp;Geocommunicator&rsquo;s existing support contract expires in March.&nbsp; WO 300 has been paying this contract but it supports data that is not owned by WO 300.&nbsp; Is WO 300 obligated to continue to support this contract?&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <o:OfficeDocumentSettings> <o:AllowPNG /> </o:OfficeDocumentSettings> </xml><![endif][if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:WordDocument> <w:View>Normal</w:View> <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom> <w:TrackMoves /> <w:TrackFormatting /> <w:PunctuationKerning /> <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas /> <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid> <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent> <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText> <w:DoNotPromoteQF /> <w:LidThemeOther>EN-