d that the Public Affairs team was the lead in coordinating efforts regarding the internal and external sites.<span>&nbsp; </span>They have staff that provides needed support to keep the sharepoint site up and running.<span>&nbsp; </span>I asked if they had resources that we could leverage and he wasn&rsquo;t sure (but that may be because he cant make that call).</span></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>Geospatial Publication Investment</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with Joe Manke and Beth on 2/21/12 in regards to the request for information for the funding of future budgets.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with Beth, Don, Mike, Ronnie, Kim and John B to discuss the presentation for GPI at the ITIB.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with Carmel Walters on 2/22/12 to discuss the project charter as they were packaging it for signature.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Worked with Beth and team 2/21/12 -2/24/12 in order to update ITIB documents and the presentation.<span>&nbsp; </span>Coordinated several impromtu meetings to ensure that WO300 and WO500 were on the same page.<span>&nbsp; </span>Provided updates to the charter and the presentation.<span>&nbsp; </span>Provided research for costs along with research information for RFI\'s and Contracts.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>Field Focused Team</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with the Field Focused team to discuss document tracking system efforts on 2/22/12.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>Quicktime Information Bulletin</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Composed an Information Bulletin in regards to the authorized use of remote access to Quicktime.<span> </span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span><span><br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>Social Media</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Provide summary of meeting with Aaron Haselby to Al\'Tariq on 2/21/12.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>Geospatial Publication Investment</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with Joe Manke and Beth on 2/21/12 in regards to the request for information for the funding of future budgets.<span>&nbsp; </span>This clarified that the spreadsheets are forms used across the board by CPIC so they were not requesting information for upcoming years for this project. The NOC was aware that this was the last year for GeoCommunicator and that there would be a new spreadsheet when GPI becomes a project.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with Beth, Don, Mike, Ronnie, Kim and John B to discuss the presentation for GPI at the ITIB.<span>&nbsp; </span>Ronnie was excited about how well the teams had worked together.<span>&nbsp; </span>She suggested that we add a break line on the presentation to show that we were only discussing Planning and Requirements at this point.<span>&nbsp; </span>She understood that Execution included Design - O&amp;M and that potion would be broken out after the GPI team returned after the Planning Phase.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with Carmel Walters on 2/22/12 to discuss the project charter as they were packaging it for signature.<span>&nbsp; </span>We discussed BLM\'s format and WO570\'s format.<span>&nbsp; </span>She wanted to ensure that is was in the format that we wanted.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Coordinated several impromtu meetings to ensure that WO300 and WO500 were on the same page.<span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>Field Focused Team</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with the Field Focused team to discuss document tracking system efforts on 2/22/12.<span>&nbsp; </span>Mohammad suggested that we use a system developed by Lewis Technologies(Atechra).<span>&nbsp; </span>This was a sharepoint system previously viewed by some staff members.<span>&nbsp; </span>There is a requirements document that is provided with this.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>Social Media</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with Aaron Haselby from Oregon on 2/17/12 in regards to their Intranet.<span>&nbsp; </span>Provide summary to Al\'Tariq on 2/21/12.<span>&nbsp; </span>Aaron stated that they use sharepoint for their internal site and that the Public Affairs staff handles the information.<span>&nbsp; </span>The Public Affairs staff posts the information twice (internally and externally).<span>&nbsp; </span>He also said that the Public Affairs team was the lead in coordinating efforts regarding the internal and external sites.<span>&nbsp; </span>They have staff that provides needed support to keep the sharepoint site up and running.<span>&nbsp; </span>I asked if they had resources that we could leverage and he wasn&rsquo;t sure (but that may be because he cant make that call).</span></p>', '<p>na</p>', '<p>na</p>', '2', '2', '2012-02-24 22:06:08', '3', '2012-04-02 20:52:59');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('27', '13', '2', '1', '2012-03-16', '<p>Began reading about the BLM Systems Lifecycle Management Framework early in the week.</p>\r\n<p>Day 1 in office:&nbsp; Thursday Meet and greet, read, discussion.</p>\r\n<p>Day 2 in office:&nbsp; Met with Mr. Samuels and Mr. Eichenbaum; clarifying meetings wiith Mr. Lewis.&nbsp; Went to GSA to get HSPD12 badging process started.</p>', '<p>Began an edit of the SLM Framework document, primarily raising questions/clarifying concepts, identifying points of potential confusion.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>No Presentations, brief meet and greet meetings with various BLM personnel.</p>', '<p>None<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> .</span></p>', '<p>None.</p>', '2', '4', '2012-03-13 16:00:54', '13', '2012-03-20 16:54:34');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('28', '12', '2', '1', '2012-03-16', '<pre><pre><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0.25in 6pt 0in; tab-stops: 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt;\"><span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Main activities conducted this week included review of the </span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0.25in 6pt 0in; tab-stops: 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt;\"><span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">BLM </span></span><span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">System Lifecycle Management Framework User\'s Manual, </span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0.25in 6pt 0in; tab-stops: 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt;\"><span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Technical </span></span><span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Manual, the IRM Reference Manual<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>and WO-570 </span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0.25in 6pt 0in; tab-stops: 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt;\"><span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">project information.  </span></span><span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Mr. Lewis has recommended </span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0.25in 6pt 0in; tab-stops: 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt;\"><span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">that an additional week be taken to review SLM materials and </span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0.25in 6pt 0in; tab-stops: 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt;\"><span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">become better acquainted with the BLM.</span></span></p></span></pre>\r\n<pre><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></pre>\r\n</pre>', '<p><span>I began editing portions of sections 1-3 of the System Lifecycle Management (SRM) technical manual.&nbsp; An informal structured walkthrough review of edits with Atechra personnel is&nbsp;scheduled for the week of 3/19.</span></p>', '<p><span>WO-570 Director Al\' Tariq Samuels held an initial overview meeting for new Atechra employees Paul A. McAllister and James Mattix. Kelly Lewis, and Robert Springfield were also present. Subsequent to this meeting, Mr. Samuels introduced me to the new IT Director (Mr. Eichenbaum). The thrust of the meeting was to express WO-570 intent to include IT as well as other key stakeholders in early phases of project planning and also to establish WO-570 intent to update the SLM.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Mr. Samuels also introduced me to representatives in the Network Operations Center or NOC.</span></p>', '<p><span>If current issues are&nbsp;unresolved, I&nbsp;would like additional support to obtain a permanent contractor DOI badge. The BLM Human Resources team suggested that I will have to complete an SF-85P unless the process for obtaining a Public Trust clearance has been fully addressed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span>None</span></p>', '2', '4', '2012-03-19 22:48:43', '12', '2012-03-20 23:17:46');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('29', '13', '2', '1', '2012-03-23', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">Began working with Pat Stingley on Data Center Consolidation Report for DOI CIO (R. Levine signature).<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Modified the individual plans for Portland (Northwest Coordination Center), Salem and Spokane Regional Offices, inputting data from several sources.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Still missing two data components, network circuits and detailed info on server specifics (make/model/SN), will have to be tracked down next week.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Contacted Doug Sipes at NOC who is known to have the WAN data; Mr. Stingley will undoubtedly have a method for obtaining server data.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">Sat in on cloud computing call with Eastern States.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>They have an approved GeoCloud II project to move a General Land Office website to the cloud.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>A heavy volume/critical function of the site is making survey data and plat maps available by lat/lon.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Previous capability was apparently lost when a software system <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>using an ESRI ArcGIS server was retired. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>New cloud offering is known to have an ArcGIS server.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Initial tasking to develop a cost model using Amazon&rsquo;s &ldquo;Simple&rdquo; price calculator was withdrawn when it was discovered that&nbsp;the price, the total storage, forecast traffic usage, # of virtualized server instances, etc were required.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>At Mr. Stingley&rsquo;s request, NOC, who had been doing some traffic forecasting, took the lead to generate the cost model. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">Continued working on an edit of the SLM.</span></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">Reached initial tentative agreement with Paul McAllister on distribution of workload, to be ratified by Mr. Samuels (and Atechra?) next week.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">Completed Data Center Consolidation closeout plans for three sites (to the extent possible at this time).</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">Had several meetings with Pat Stingley re Data Center Consolidation/Cloud Computing.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Several very brief encounters with Al&rsquo;Tariq regarding project assignments, and a brief opportunity to meet Ronnie Levine.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Paul and I had a good hallway meeting with Joe McMahon of CPIC regarding the SLM; more to come, an excellent source with deep understanding of the system lifecycle management.</span></p>', '<p>None.</p>', '<p>N/A</p>', '2', '4', '2012-03-23 22:58:27', '4', '2012-03-30 19:37:30');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('30', '12', '2', '1', '2012-03-23', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Project Assignments</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">On Friday, March 23, 2012, I initiated discussions with Brian, Naomi and Ken to determine current project assignments within WO-570.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>After verifying project assignments, I met with James Mattix and formulated the comprehensive list below.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The early draft version of the list was previously sent via email to Robert Springfield.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-yfti-tbllook: 1184; mso-padding-alt: 0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 15pt; mso-yfti-irow: 0; mso-yfti-firstrow: yes;\">\r\n<td style=\"padding-bottom: 0in; background-color: transparent; padding-left: 5.4pt; width: 443pt; padding-right: 5.4pt; height: 15pt; padding-top: 0in; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; border: windowtext 1pt solid;\" width=\"591\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">BLM WO-570 Projects</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: windowtext 1pt solid; border-left: #f0f0f0; padding-bottom: 0in; background-color: transparent; padding-left: 5.4pt; width: 114pt; padding-right: 5.4pt; height: 15pt; border-top: windowt