:34', null, '2012-07-12 22:08:12');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('66', '13', '2', '1', '2012-07-13', '<p><span>Performed final edit to ILM document; believe it is ready for outside review, especially review &amp; discussion with NOC.&nbsp; Will require one final polish to correct spacing, minor layout issues after changes are accepted/rejected by Ms. Bowers.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>ICW Data Center Closings, directed by Mr. Samuels to put together a meeting between NOC, 570, 580 and&nbsp;Eastern States Office&nbsp;regarding closure of ESSO, General Land Office (GLO)&nbsp;and WO Data Centers; mtng scheduled for 7/18.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Mr. Samuels requested all 570 staff review the new OMB document \"Collaborative Planning Methodology\".&nbsp; Started reviewing Friday; made me feel confident that the ILM doc is in good shape.&nbsp; Surprising amount of unclear and ungrammatical writing from OMB.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Began working on 2012 FDCCI plan; started an edit of the document, need meeting w/Mr. Stingley to proceed.</span></p>', '<p><span>Produced signature-ready closing documents for next six Data Center Consolidation Initiative sites, due 9/30.&nbsp; This should eliminate the last minute crunch of the last two quarters, allowing the NOC to proceed with addressing actual closings. (All sites&nbsp;thus far&nbsp;were&nbsp;previously closed in 2011).</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Finalized ILM(?) Hopefully.</span></p>', '<p><span>Review meeting (telecon)&nbsp;with DOI PMs&nbsp;to review&nbsp;this quarter\'s Data Center Closing documents.&nbsp; Some controversy regarding growth from 3-to 4 servers in sites that were \"closing\", and on the&nbsp;application of telecom charges; we applied all upgrade costs to the closing, (resulting in negative ROI);&nbsp;they questioned whether the cost increases were due to moving databases off site, or merely needed bandwidth upgrades.&nbsp; Oregon data administrator won the arguments by pointing out that the&nbsp;closing docs&nbsp;only reported the configuration from the&nbsp;last year, but&nbsp;BLM Oregon consolidation had been going on since 2008, all sites now in final statewide&nbsp;configuration of 1 file/print server, 1 DNS1 server, 1 Network Probe, 1 SAN. Previously, when GIS data was moved from local servers to Portland data center, went from 1 to 2 T-1 configuration, necessary Bandwidth increase to handle the transfer of large GIS files.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Weekly teleconference with DOI PMs for DCCI; nothing controversial, reviewed dates for next submissions.</span></p>', '<p>None</p>', '<p>N/A</p>', '2', '4', '2012-07-16 11:42:48', '4', '2012-07-18 21:56:32');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('67', '14', '8', '1', '2012-07-13', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\">AFMSS - Worked on the&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">quality management approach to ensure the quality assurance (QA) services for the AFMSS project in accordance with the<span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.05pt;\"> </span>Institute<span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.05pt;\"> </span>of<span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.05pt;\"> </span>Electrical<span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.05pt;\"> </span>and<span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.05pt;\"> </span>Electronics Engineers (IEEE) and the Project Ma<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.05pt;\">n</span>age<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.1pt;\">m</span>ent Instit<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.05pt;\">u</span>te (PMI) guidlines.&nbsp;&nbsp; Worked on the</span></span></span><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\"> a</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">cquisition s</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">trategy to document and inform project stakeholders about how the acquisitions will be planned, executed, and managed throughout the lifecycle of the project. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\">AFMSS&nbsp; APD - Worked on the revised cost analysis.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\">MDT - Finalized documentation for release to COTR.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\">Tablet PC - Signature required for ITIB IM.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\">Radio - Worked on the tactical framework documentation for initial review.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\">AFMSS - Completed update to the <span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">quality assurance (QA) approach, which included the following components: Action Plan, Reporting Plan.</span></span></span><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\">MDT -&nbsp;COTR release PR to CO.</span><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; font-size: 12pt;\">Tablet PC - Released/published ITIB IM.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>MDT - Weekly Law Enforcement Project Team meeting. 7/10</p>', '<p>AFMSS: None</p>\r\n<p>AFMSS APD: None</p>\r\n<p>MDT: None</p>\r\n<p>Tablet PC: None</p>\r\n<p>Radio - Need assistance determining strategic goals priorities.</p>', '<p>AFMSS: None</p>\r\n<p>AFMSS APD: None</p>\r\n<p>MDT: None</p>\r\n<p>Tablet PC: None</p>\r\n<p>Radio - Need assistance determining strategic goals priorities.</p>', '2', '4', '2012-07-17 09:16:39', null, '2012-07-18 21:57:23');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('68', '13', '2', '1', '2012-07-20', '<p>Completed review of OMB document \"Collaborative Planning Methodology.&nbsp; Discussed its quality with Ms. Hawkinson, also reviewing; we agreed the document is really not ready for distribution outside OMB.&nbsp; Some sections are so poorly written as to be virtually unreadable.&nbsp; Turned in two dozen comments with explanations on the comment sheet they provided.&nbsp; Going further would have required literally rewriting the document; don\'t think that was the assignment.</p>\r\n<p>Began working up documents in template form for creating the basics of&nbsp; the Enterprise Architecture for Mr. Stingley.&nbsp; This is a major effort, will require significant amounts of time designing format, structure...before even beginning to collect data about systems.&nbsp; Considering designing the system as a geospatial map, given the broad dispersion of BLM offices; click on an office and drill down into the local data.&nbsp; This will be an ongoing effort similar in scope to ILM effort.</p>', '<p>Finished the OMB doc.</p>\r\n<p>Started two new efforts.</p>', '<p>7/18 Meeting requested by Mr. Samuels regarding the data center closures and office moves of ESSO and GLO to 20 M St.&nbsp;was successful in clarifying move plans, identified a potential problem area in the closure.&nbsp; GLO will be moving to a new office not colocated with 20 M.&nbsp; The nature of their effort; scanning docs into servers, will create the appearance of building a new data center, as the Servers MUST be colocated in physical proximity with the scanners.&nbsp; This move was news and will require a waiver from DOI/OMB.</p>\r\n<p>Assignment from biweekly staff meeting from Mr. Samuels for Stingley, Bowers, Mattix to meet, discuss an ILM approach to the states (ILM is for national efforts). States have their own internal processes which we will not govern, but will need to track and assist where possible.&nbsp; Discussed the fact that states have significant resistance to letting anyone know what they are up to, for fear of becoming \"National Projects\".&nbsp; Agreed we would need to loosen that definition (use by more than one state creates de jure national project. We identified the kinds of documents that WO/EA/PMO would need to receive for filing in the EA repository, and coordinating with CPIC/Security&nbsp;agreed that we would need a separate, shorter document than the ILM, Mattix tasked with drafting same.</p>', '<p>None</p>', '<p>N/A</p>', '2', '4', '2012-07-23 11:41:04', '4', '2012-07-27 09:45:27');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('69', '2', '8', '1', '2012-07-20', '<p>DOI IRM Scorecard - Developed appeal on DOI BLM IRM Scorecard for items which were not in compliance.&nbsp; The BLM appeals areas were as follows:&nbsp; Building on Prior year Goals; FDCCI; Accountability; SO-3309; and ITT Areas &ndash; Radio.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;BLM IT Portfolio Management - Working group on efficiencies in the IT investment area.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">MDT:&nbsp; Worked on acquisition plan.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Tablet PC: Worked on BLMTablet PC validation activies.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Radio - Worked on tactical plan documentation.</p>', '<p>DOI IRM Scorecard - Submitted Appeal report to DCIO DOI.</p>\r\n<p>MDT: Submitted acquistion plan to procurement.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tablet PC: Submitted BLM Tablet PC acquisitions and validation to the DOI.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>DOI IRM Scorecard - Meeting 7/17/2012..</p>\r\n<p>BLM IT Portfolio Management: 7/12/2012</p>\r\n<p>WO-570 Staff Meeting: 7/13/2012</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>DOI IRM Scorecard - None</p>\r\n<p>AFMSS: None</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>AFMSS APD: None</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>MDT: None</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tablet PC: None</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Radio - Need assistance determining strategic goals priorities.</p>', '<p>DOI IRM Scorecard - None</p>\r\n<p>AFMSS: None</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>AFMSS APD: None</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>MDT: None</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tablet PC: None</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Radio - Need assistance determining strategic goals priorities.</p>', '2', '4', '2012-07-25 13:44:51', '4', '2012-07-27 09:46:45');
