INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('133', '16', '2', '1', '2012-11-30', '<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">For the Project Portfolio project, I reviewed the document of Wild Horse and Burro Information System (WHBIS) application to understand the status of the WHBIS.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Met with Ken Greenberger to find a history of Wild Horse and Burro for better understanding of the WHBIS application.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">For Project Portfolio project, I am reviewing mission need statement and other documents for SPATS.&nbsp; Mohammad and I will be meeting with business manager to get more understating about this project.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</p>', '<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Reviewed the mission need statement and other documents for SPATS.</span></p>\r\n</p>', '<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Met with Ken Greenberger to discuss a history of Wild Horse and Burro.</span></p>\r\n</p>', '<p>n/a</p>', '<p>n/a</p>', '2', '1', '2012-11-30 15:37:09', '19', '2012-12-04 21:53:11');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('134', '13', '2', '1', '2012-11-30', '<p>Spent the entire week implementing the ILM changes requested in the IRT meeting. &nbsp;A bad MS Word save on Wed cost almost two days\' work, when the document went from 120 PP. to 13.. The help desk recovered the file from the previous night\'s backup, so I was able to save a considerable amount of the previous week\'s alteration.</p>\r\n<p>This iteration involved adding considerable material and graphics from Mr. Samuels presentation to ITIB, numerous other small changes. Should be able to complete the document by next Tuesday or so, on schedule, per the promise made at the IRT meeting.</p>', '<p>Saved the ILM.</p>', '<p>None.</p>', '<p>None.</p>', '<p>None.</p>', '2', '1', '2012-12-03 15:41:22', '19', '2012-12-04 21:52:59');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('135', '2', '8', '1', '2012-11-30', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>MDT - Worked on resolving IMARS reporting via iPads problem. &nbsp;Citrix connection is too slow for law enforcement submit the required reports.</p>\r\n<p>WO570 - Assisted with administrative task in support of IT planning.</p>\r\n<p>Tablet PC - Worked on survey reports for law enforcement pilot.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Tablet PC - completed law enforcement survey report</p>', '<p>MDT - Bi-weekly team meeting.</p>', '<p>MDT - Contract activities are not clear.</p>', '<p>None.</p>', '2', '1', '2012-12-04 21:51:48', null, '2012-12-04 21:52:46');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('136', '16', '18', '6', '2012-12-07', '<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">In order to effectively implement Project Portfolio Management (PPM) at BLM, I attended the one day training session by Forrester Research group about Portfolio Management 101.&nbsp; This training session introduced common terminology of Project Portfolio Management, Enterprise Portfolio Management and Key metrics used in the PPM implementation.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">I met with Mohammad Haniffa to discuss how we can implement Project Portfolio Management based on our training from Forrester.&nbsp; Mohammad has given me one data file with inventory of applications and projects across the BLM.&nbsp; I have been tasked with summarizing data based on the format given by him.&nbsp; I also need to add more data based on the mission critical application data that we had collected few months back.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Created an initial draft of summary dataset for Mohammad&rsquo;s review and feedback based on the dataset the information provided.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Based on initial draft&rsquo;s approval, I create summary for all the states and national applications in the database. &nbsp;I have also included Mission critical dataset in this database.&nbsp; This would be useful in&nbsp; stage 1&nbsp;to acquire knowledge for further analysis of Portfolio Analysis.&nbsp; I would meet with Mohammad next week to see what further actions are necessary based on his feedback.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>', '<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Sent Initial draft of summary to Mohammad to review before spending more time to gather more data from the spreadsheet for BLM&rsquo;s application and project status.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Based on feedback of initial draft, provided interim report to Mohammad for his review.&nbsp; Few information columns are missing information and need to discuss with Mohammad about how to get this information to do more analysis.</span></p>\r\n</p>', '<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Attended a training session for the project portfolio management by Forrester Research group for implementation of Project Portfolio Management at the BLM.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Attended a WO-570 staff meeting to discuss status of the projects and get update from Al&rsquo;Tariq on current projects/status.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</p>', '<p>n/a</p>', '<p>n/a</p>', '2', '4', '2012-12-07 15:34:39', '4', '2012-12-17 20:54:18');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('137', '13', '17', '5', '2012-12-07', '<p>I submitted a New draft of ILM Monday, which was immediately distributed by Ms. Bowers to the IRT team for review. After a couple of days, I suggested placing a deadline for response and was told to do so, so I notified the team of a response date for next week, COB 12/11</p>\r\n<p>In the meantime, I accepted all changes in the ILM and corrected spacing, ran spelling/grammar check and corrected TOC and TOF. &nbsp;Plan is to integrate any further changes from IRT team and send to state offices for a short comment period; incorporate changes and publish, hopefully in mid-late January.</p>\r\n<p>See meetings section for background: &nbsp;Began working on closure docs for last minute acceleration of two sites from 3Q \'13 to 1Q \'13 (12/31/12). Many discrepencies in first site (AZ State Office); meeting next week to clarify, following week for second site..</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Completed ILM Draft</p>', '<p>Wednesday FDCCI telecon was a bit unusual. &nbsp;I was only BLM representative. &nbsp;It was noted to me by the Lead that BLM owed two site closures at the end of the month, and where did we stand with that? This was absolutely contrary to our plan and I said so, noting that the plan we turned in for 2013 in September showed that we were in a six month hiatus for closures, the next sites due 6/30/13. &nbsp;Generated a bit of controversy. &nbsp;I notified Mr. Stingley,and sent email to the PM asking if he had made schedule changes (NO). &nbsp;Several email exchanges followed, between PM and Roger Franklin, DOI FDCCI PM, Lillie Martinez, DOI Lead, Mr. Stingley, resulting in escalation to Mr. Samuels, Ms. Jollay and Ms. Finnefrock on Thursday.</p>\r\n<p>Briefed Mr. Samuels on background Fri AM, he and Mr. Stingley came to me later to lay out a strategy and ask me to begin working on several documents necessary for the plan. &nbsp;More Next week.</p>', '<p>None</p>', '<p>COTR is aware of FDCCI issue and has a strategy that I will be supporting with documentation.</p>', '2', '4', '2012-12-07 15:43:43', '4', '2012-12-17 20:58:10');
