INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('139', '16', '18', '6', '2012-12-14', '<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">I have been tasked with summarizing application data for entire BLM based on two earlier data call inventory list.&nbsp; This is a part of exercise for implementing Project Portfolio Management at BLM.&nbsp; Last week, I started to combine two inventory lists and create a single database.&nbsp; I have continued to work this creating this database this week.&nbsp; I have sent this database to Mohammad so he can populate this on the SharePoint Site.&nbsp; I will continue to work this database to eliminate duplications next week.&nbsp; We will present this database to Al&rsquo;Tariq next week. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Mohammad and I met with Kathie Jewell from WO-200 to discuss Roles and responsibility change in the WO-570.&nbsp; Mohammad introduced&nbsp;me as a Project Manager for most of the WO-200.&nbsp; Kathie will start include me in the Science Permit Application and Tracking System (SPATS) and other WO-200 projects.&nbsp; I have contacted Neffra Matthews to discuss project status of SPATS.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">I had a teleconference with Mohammad about next steps for the Project Portfolio Management.&nbsp; Mohammad had laid out three-four action items for next 3-4 weeks.</span></p>\r\n</p>', '<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Database for the entire BLM IT application is about 75% ready.&nbsp; I have populated few more columns and added national application from all the states in this database.&nbsp; Next step is to remove duplication from the database.</span></p>\r\n</p>', '<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Al&rsquo;Tariq Samuels called a meeting to discuss progress status and future steps needed to implement Project Portfolio at BLM.&nbsp; This meeting was attended by Mohammad, Mike Landry, Chintan Mody and Sayed.&nbsp; In this meeting, we discussed future steps and their deadline to initiate Project Portfolio implementation at the BLM.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Mohammad, Kathie Jewell (WO-200) and I met to discuss </span><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Science Permit Application and Tracking System (SPATS) and other WO-200 projects.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">I had a conference call with Mohammad to discuss next steps for the Project Portfolio Management framework and action items.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</p>', '<p>n/a</p>', '<p>n/a</p>', '2', '4', '2012-12-14 15:13:15', '4', '2012-12-17 21:06:08');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` VALUES ('140', '13', '17', '5', '2012-12-14', '<p>Planning for next site closures with Denver Project Manager for the Data Center Consolidation Initiative (DCCI). Had one preliminary review meeting this week, and have scheduled initial closing document reviews with the Arizona State Office, the California State office, and Campbell Tract, AK for next week. &nbsp;Did an extensive desktop review and edit of the AZSO documents, prepping for next week.</p>\r\n<p>Received new project assignments for the EGIS and GPM projects (both involve aspects of Internet dissemination of Geospatial data for staff and the pubilc). &nbsp;Began studying available documentation in prep for initial meetings next week.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed first set of comments on the Integrated Lifecycle Management (ILM) Framework from Information Assurance Div. &nbsp;Thoughtful, thorough, useful edits, all.</p>\r\n<p>Shipped documentation to CA state IT Director regarding DCCI activities, to bring him up to speed; through his presence on the \"Hosting Committee\" (seeking large facilities for Department-wide consolidation) he has somehow become involved in DCC activities. Mr. Samuels spoke with him and has asked me to do a phone briefing in the next couple of days.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>At the&nbsp; request of the CTO,delivered draft Change Request to CTO/Div. Dir. to recognize that the 2013 DCCI plan we turned in to DOI in September was, in fact, a rebaselining of our original plans. &nbsp;Under review.</p>\r\n<p>Delivered first draft funding request to support engineering design/pilot test for delivery/support of unified enterprise level Geospatial Information data system.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Excellent meeting with Mr. Samuels and our Portfolio Management Team resulted in new assignments (discussed earlier), better understanding and an outstanding demonstration of support and commitment to our team.</p>\r\n<p>Had initial telecon with AZSO to review their closure docs, plan timelines, understand their real configuration; believe they are now well positioned to successfully close the site by 12/31.</p>\r\n<p>Brief meeting with Mr. Samuels to review status of DCCI site closures for end of year, since Mr. Stingley is out until January. &nbsp;Also reviewed plans to brief CA State Director on DCCI.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>None</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>N/A</p>', '2', '4', '2012-12-14 16:04:20', '4', '2012-12-17 21:02:44');
